The public has been warned to exercise caution when visiting
dams, rivers, streams, rivers, or lakes. This is after a man's body was discovered in a river stream
in Kriel on Saturday, 25 June 25. According to cops, on 13 June 2022 a local pastor from Kriel,
together with another man are said to have gone to the river streams to pray. However, the man that the pastor went with somehow fell and
drowned. Although the matter was reported to the authorities, his body could
not be recovered then by members of the Police Diving Unit. ALSO READ |
Zuma plans to take fight PHAMBILI! “The search for the man continued for days without any
success until the divers finally retrieved his body,” cops spokesman Brigadier
Selvy Mohlala said. Mohlala said the man has since been identified as Eric
Phaswane, aged 43 from Thubelihle in Kriel and cops have opened an inquest case
following the sad incident. Provincial Commissioner of the SAPS in Mpumalanga,
Lieutenant General Semakaleng Daphney Manamela pleaded with the public to
consider the shower rains that were experienced in some parts of the province
which made the dams and rivers swell.